Package: LAMBDAR
Type: Package
Title: Measure galaxy fluxes from an arbitrary FITS image using input aperture locations and dimensions
Version: 0.1
Date: 2014-01-09
Author: Angus H. Wright
Maintainer: Angus H. Wright <angus.wright@icrar.org>
Description: LAMBDAR (Lambda Adaptive Multi-Band Detection Algorithm in R) is a proceedure for measuring the fluxes of galaxies in an arbitrary FITS image, covering an arbitrary photometric wave-band, when provided all paramters needed to construct galactic apertures at the required locations.
Depends: astro, doParallel, foreach, magicaxis, nortest
License: GPL-2
Packaged: 2013-10-23 14:30:43 UTC; awright
